  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      Cesarean section on demand: defined as a primary cesarean section performed at the mother's
      request to avoid a vaginal birth, without any recognized medical or obstetric indication. The
      medical field now acknowledges a patient's right to actively participate in her choice of
      medical treatments, including method of delivery.

      There are many reasons for a cesarean section on demand: fear of delivery, fear of pain,
      family pressure, a previous bad experience, more control over events, improved care, and
      maintaining the integrity of the pelvic floor. of the pelvic floor.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
